FBIS4-41556 "drsov123_b_94027" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS Nuclear & Military Issues Over 270 AES Emergencies Recorded in 2-Year Period Over 270 AES Emergencies Recorded in 2-Year Period LD2606164494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2606164494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Excerpt] Over the past two years, over 270 emergencies have been recorded at Russian nuclear power stations, including five involving leakages of radioactive substances into the outside world. These sad figures were cited by Vladimir Kuznetsov, a former employee of the State Committee for the Supervision of Nuclear and Radiation Safety, at the presentation of his book entitled: State Radiation [Gosudarstvennaya Radiatsiya]. [passage omitted]
